text:
- bannon got it immediately. he believes in the whole andrew breitbart doctrine that politics is downstream from culture, so to change politics you need to change culture. and fashion trends are a useful proxy for that. trump is like a pair of uggs, or crocs, basically. so how do you get from people thinking ‘ugh. totally ugly’ to the moment when everyone is wearing them? that was the inflection point he was looking for.

is what cambridge analytica does akin to bullying? - i think it’s worse than bullying, christopher wylie says. - because people don’t necessarily know it’s being done to them. at least bullying respects the agency of people because they know. so it’s worse, because if you do not respect the agency of people, anything that you’re doing after that point is not conducive to a democracy. and fundamentally, information warfare is not conducive to democracy.

millions of people’s personal information was stolen and used to target them in ways they wouldn’t have seen, and couldn’t have known about, by a mercenary outfit, cambridge analytica, who, wylie says, “would work for anyone”. who would pitch to russian oil companies. would they subvert elections abroad on behalf of foreign governments?

it occurs to me to ask wylie this one night. - yes.

nato or non-nato? - either. i mean they’re mercenaries. they’ll work for pretty much anyone who pays.

it’s an incredible revelation. it also encapsulates all of the problems of outsourcing – at a global scale, with added cyberweapons. and in the middle of it all are the public – our intimate family connections, our “likes”, our crumbs of personal data, all sucked into a swirling black hole that’s expanding and growing and is now owned by a politically motivated billionaire.

carole cadwalladr
the guardian

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby," said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
healthy choice-
margaret sanger gave us a choice-  planned parenthood- in 1916, she opened the first birth control clinic in the united states. ... around this time, sanger also published her first issue of the birth control review. in 1921, sanger established the american birth control league, a precursor to today's planned parenthood federation of america.
she was one of 11 children born into a roman catholic working-class irish american family. her mother, anne, had several miscarriages, and margaret believed that all of these pregnancies took a toll on her mother's health and contributed to her early death at the age of 40 (some reports say 50). the family lived in poverty as her father, michael, an irish stonemason, preferred to drink and talk politics than earn a steady wage. margaret became a nurse and devoted her life to women’s rights and the freedom of choice- 
healthy choice- .
.

text:
è uscito ieri in libreria e io l'ho ricevuto in anteprima dalla casa editrice @tre60_libri che ringrazio perché ho amato tantissimo questo libro, letto in un lampo non perché sia breve ma perché particolarmente intenso. 
è un fumetto nato dal talento delle autrici norvegesi marta breen e jenny jordahl e racconta 150 anni di lotte per l'emancipazione femminile.

personalmente, non mi sono mai sentita "femminista", mi pareva sufficiente potermi soltanto identificare in un essere umano chiamato noemi. però andando avanti nella vita e leggendo queste pagine ho sentito inevitabilmente purtroppo anche il bisogno di ricordarmi il valore di appartenere a una minoranza che fino a pochissimo (dà i brividi sapere quanto poco) tempo fa non poteva studiare, lavorare, votare e disporre con libertà del proprio corpo. 
il libro ci ricorda le conquiste di donne forti e coraggiose ma anche quanto in alcuni paesi (il nostro incluso?) ci sia tanto ma tanto ancora da fare. 
dalle suffragette al premio nobel per la pace alla diciassettenne malala, dalle battaglie per il diritto allo studio al movimento #metoo, è stato emozionante e doloroso, entusiasmante e difficile leggere questa storia che ci tocca tutti grazie anche alle immagini che a volte, neanche a dirlo, esprimono più di molte parole.

visto che si avvicina la festa della donna, e il fumetto ne spiega il significato, io lo regalerei il più possibile a tutti per acuire  la sensibilità verso le donne, questi esseri umani, tutte noi, meritevoli di spazi, rispetto e diritti in ogni tempo.

#donne #femminismo #metoo #libri #fumetti #8marzo 🌾

text:
at qut we’ve been covering the campus in posters for some of our upcoming events like “the system behind sexism” and “marxism, socialism, revolution: the case for radical politics”. on tuesday the 26th of february @ 6pm our meeting “the system behind sexism” will be held at 136 boundary street in west end. sexism is everywhere. the gender pay gap is at a two-decade high, women in australia still perform seven times more housework than men and #metoo provoked a global discussion of the sexual violence and harassment that is part of life for women the world over. capitalism couldn't exist without the oppression of women and the whole gender binary. if you're outraged by gender inequality, come join socialist alternative for a discussion of where it comes from and how we can smash it.

our campus meetings on “marxism, socialism, revolution: the case for radical politics” will be held at the gardens point campus at s block room 308 on wednesday 27th of february @ 1pm. it will also be held on the kelvin grove campus at n block room 517 on the 28th of february at 1pm. we currently live in a society of mass inequality, racism, sexism, environmental destruction and the exploitation of millions around the world. everywhere people are searching for an alternative, but what kind do we need and what would it look like? this meeting will be about introducing the ideas of and answering your questions about marxism, socialism and revolution and why we need radical politics to change the system. all progressives welcome!

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytical $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
in his first post-white house interviews, steve bannon, the rightwing ideologue who helped propel donald trump to the white house, made clear that he had no intention of going quietly. - i’ve got my hands back on my weapons, the former white house chief strategist, who returned as executive chairman of breitbart news late friday afternoon, told the weekly standard. - i built a f***ing machine at breitbart. and now i’m about to go back, knowing what i know, and we’re about to rev that machine up. and rev it up we will do.

just hours after his departure from the trump administration became public, breitbart, whose traffic and advertising have fallen significantly since trump’s election, trumpeted the return of their “populist hero” on its homepage. - the populist-nationalist movement got a lot stronger today, breitbart editor-in-chief alex marlow said in the publication’s announcement post. - breitbart gained an executive chairman with his finger on the pulse of the trump agenda.

the fall of steve bannon is a win for the globalists. but will it last?

also on friday, the once-again head of breitbart told bloomberg news: - if there’s any confusion out there, let me clear it up: i’m leaving the white house and going to war for trump against his opponents – on capitol hill, in the media, and in corporate america.

the 63-year-old also retains the backing of hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. the pair met on wednesday to plot their future plans, bloomberg reported.

julia carrie wong
the guardian

text_retweet:
repost @jaringanmuda
suarakan hak kita perempuan indonesia 🇮🇩 #emmawarokka #emmania #empoweringwomen
.
.
.
.
setiap orang berhak mendapatkan rasa
aman atas bentuk tubuh dan ekspresi gender, begitu pula dengan cara berpakaian dan ekspresi tubuh yang
lain. oleh karenanya pelabelan negatif seperti gambar diatas merupakan bentuk pelecehan seksual.

tidak ada "perempuan nakal, binal, bispak, sundal"!! .
.
dalam lingkungan masyarakat yang masih patriarkis, kita sering mendengar pelabelan negatif (stereotype) tersebut. perempuan yang mendapat stereotip seperti ini lebih rentan terhadap tindak pelecehan, karena masyarakat sendiri bahkan membenarkan tindak pelecehan terhadap perempuan yang mereka labeli demikian.

stereotype tersebut salah dan tidak dapat dijadikan landasan bagi siapapun untuk membenarkan tindak pelecehan seksual terhadap orang lain. label "perempuan baik-baik" ataupun "nakal, binal, bispak, sundal" adalah cerminan konstruksi sosial yang tidak setara, merupakan bentuk penghakiman moral dan kontrol terhadap tubuh perempuan.

text:
*shy* i have never really felt it. i have always been this girl who speak up, bold, speak up, loud, even speaks up, rubbish. but never really felt shy!! .
but, living in this world of 100 opportunities to speak up? how many of us are able to do it? so, this happened yesterday. i was crossing the road after leaving my house focusing on not twisting my ankle on the road or getting hit by a car, my mind was busy so was my hands carrying two heavy bags. right then a car crossed by, puts his window down and hoots *woooooowwwwwwww*. now, it took me time to take it in and before i could react he was gone! but i was angry and irritated and annoyed, yes i could have made a huge scene or made a big deal out of it or may be i should have. but "boss i seriously had no time for that shit", so now that i'm processing it in will the guys who did it or the passerby think that i'm just too shy to respond and could do take an action towards it? was my busy and occupied mind at a moment letting me be weak? i don't know i'm confused. .
.
sharing my experience, to all boys and girls out there. it's not easy to be a lady!
#speakup #girlstalkloud #wewontshutup #notshuttingup #metoo #wtfguys #notimeforshit #notshynomore #shutthebullshitdown #womensday2019 #balanceforbetter #womensafety #indianwomensayit #stopshuttingup #sayitall #hidefromnoone #fearnoone #girlsspeakup #itsnotokay #consent
#womensafestreets #arewereallyshy #shyforwhat #stopthisnow

text: jeg vil takke alle som kom for å høre på oss i @hva.snakker.du.om (og @erleslagsvold & @witchcrvvft ) på @samfunnetbislet i går. det var latter og tårer om hverandre og vi fikk høre at vi virkelig gjorde inntrykk, noe som var et av målene med denne temakvelden. jeg snakket om noe som jeg aldri har snakket om på en scene før, noe som fortsatt er sårt og vanskelig til tider. jeg mener det er viktig at man snakker om ting som er vanskelig, uansett om det er på en scene, med en venn, en forelder eller en fremmed. vi skal ikke skamme oss over at livet er kjipt av og til, for det er jo et faktum for oss alle. søk tilflukt, søk hjelp, vær ærlig - i hvert fall med deg selv. ✊🏻✊🏻✊🏻 #storytelling #fortelling #stage #microphone #tabu #tabubelagte #temaer #søk #hjelp #og #snakk #om #det #tusentakk #til #alle #som #kom #bestrong #speakup #metoo

text:
...
i had a talk with a close friend of mine recently and she has the misfortune of having to parallel parent with a person who expresses several narcissistic traits
.
i am not a psychologist so i am not diagnosing her ex, but this dude is as toxic and neurotic as they come
.
he pulls classic narc tactics like, what ross rosenberg a psychologist and an expert on narcissistic personality disorders, described as “induced conversations”
.
it’s basically a hoovering tactic to reel you into a conversation under the guise that it’s a regular conversation, fake apologies or fake “revelations” with the goal to elicit a response or a defense in order to manipulate and dominate their target
.
in the case of my friend. the ex narc responded to a question about their child, via text, but before exiting the conversation found it necessary to inform my friend that he “now realizes how emotionally damaged he is from their relationship” 😳
.
i’m soooo very proud of this friend because she did not get sucked in this time. she totally ignored the comment and did not respond or react. i can’t wait for the day when she can sever all ties with this person
.
she did not engage him and the narc experienced a narcissistic injury and an epic fail at his attempt to elicit narcissistic supply from her (silly narcissist 🤣🤣🤣 we’re on to you)
.
this message is for anyone out their who is unable to completely detach and go no contact with the narcissist because they have children together, don’t engage the narcissist. protect your peace. stand in your power and focus on your own soul care and self love. if you’re still living with the narc, just know you can not heal in the same place that’s making you ill ✅
.
that is how you gain traction on your journey to happy healed and whole again 🙌🏾 mmkay?
.
#abuseawareness #narcissistfree #darktriad #traumabond #gaslighting #redflags #hoovering #nocontact #domesticviolence #covertnarcissism #abusedwomen #abusedmen #toxicpeople #npd #triangulation #empaths #metoo #enoughisenough #taradmcleod

text: "why? because when victimhood has been given social currency, people will seek it. cashing in on sympathy, support, and understanding." it is known as "victimhood chic". i grew up on foklore and fairy tales. when a story ends, i often turn the lesson introspective. have i played victim? yes. have i sought attention and recognition? sometimes no but all the time yes. am i satisfied? ...i hope so. god i really hope so. that's the insidious nature of human frailty. when is enough, enough? we don't know how far we would go to push a narrative... that part scares me. we are simultaneously our #1 champion and our mortal enemy. all i can do is to start the day hopeful, thankful, remorseful, grateful, and in praise. the lesson for me, "covet the world and lose it all". #jussiesmollett #thisisamerica #maga #blacklivesmatter #thisisus #victimhood #metoo #victimblaming #trump #theagenda #victimhoodchic

text:
​​#историичитателей

я с самого детства росла, видя насилие. отец избивал маму, у неё что только не ломалось: нос, рёбра по несколько раз. запугивал нас, детей. я всегда избегаю воспоминаний о детстве, это был ад. 
однажды я пришла из школы рано, устала (а я часто гуляла после школы на улице допоздна, чтобы прийти домой, сразу лечь спать и не видеть их опять, ссорящихся). мама лежала у порога, вся заплаканная, тушь потёкшая, а на её голове лежала огромная нога отца. он стоял перед ней и положил ногу на её лицо. я, конечно же, автоматически побежала помочь ей, но он остановил и сказал: «если подойдёшь, я раздавлю ей голову». я помню, что я просто осталась там, где стояла и помню, что не смогла помочь, но не помню, чем это закончилось.

до сих пор я вижу это во сне, до сих пор чувствую это страдание. мне тяжело строить отношения, у меня много страхов, неуверенность, боязнь, что кто-то меня ударит. хоть и работаю над собой, но эта боль теперь всегда со мной... с тех пор у меня плохие отношения и с отцом, и с мамой. почему с мамой? за то, что она всё терпела, как она говорит «ради вас». милые женщины, мамы! ваши дети не должны страдать из-за вашей низкой самооценки. они не должны видеть то, что вы позволяете с собой делать. вы не имеете права, будучи матерью, не находить силы бороться, не уходить от таких мужей. их не исправить! я – мать, и ни за что не позволю дочке видеть, как оскорбляют её маму. не терпите! =========================================

text:
exploiting women’s bodies does not promote gender equality. activists are calling on uganda’s tourism ministry to remove its miss curvy contest. 
ugandan women are livid after the country’s tourism minister godfrey kiwanda suggested promoting “curvy women” as a tourist attraction. kiwanda proposed using the miss curvy uganda beauty pageant in june to attract visitors at a press conference. now activists and ugandan women are demanding that he resign. "uganda is endowed with beautiful women. their beauty is unique and diverse,” kiwanda said, flanked by miss curvy uganda contestants. “that's why we decided to use the unique beauty, the curves... to make this beauty a product to be marketed along with what we already have as a country ranging from nature, the language and food, to make it a tourist attraction," he added.
activists claim that kiwanda’s comment does not help stop prejudices against women in the country. despite laws and efforts to protect women in uganda, gender-based violence increased by 4% between 2015 and 2016, according to the country’s police force annual crime report. "to think women can be used as sex objects in this age and time is an absurdity and we condemn it," rita aciro, executive director of the uganda women's network said.
***

text:
✔ao falar de cor: chega  como uma mensagem, declara o apoio à uma causa, como o preto no #metoo ou o rosa pink no dia internacional das mulheres. o nível de conhecimento do consumidor nunca foi tão alto, por isso a importância da autenticidade e da verdade.✔nesse mesmo contexto, outras formas de comportamento e estilo tomarão conta das ruas. a era do minimalismo dará lugar para o maximalismo dos anos 1980, com cores e padronagens em combinações excêntricas. é a liberdade para a expressão individual.
assim como a influencia do mundo digital. as pessoas estão fazendo suas compras online em cada vez menos tempo [estima-se 90 segundos para determinar a compra] e a cor geralmente influencia nessa escolha. por isso o estimulo visual se torna cada dia  mais precioso.
✔surgem as paletas de cores planejadas, como os tons de pele diferentes que a faber castell divulgou (são seis), as lingeries nude for all, da marca norte-americana naja, ou até os 40 tons de base da linha fenty beauty, marca de cosméticos da rihanna. e que tambem se aplicam ao design de interiores , essas tendencias de cores visto que tudo esta correlacionado e os espaços são criados de acordo com as mudanças sociais também.
✔ o futuro vai acontecer e a sociedade vai poder tangibilizar os avanços da tecnologia. “vamos nos inspirar cada vez mais no futuro e menos no passado. por isso temos uma paleta de cor mais otimista, versátil, revigorante com, claro, um toque futurista”, resume natalia da wgsn. as tonalidades que traduzem esse mood são o neo mint, principal aposta, seguido do purist blue, cassis, cantaloupe e mellow yellow.o azul purista , essencial na paleta para o proximo ano , cor da contemporaneidade portanto, aplica-se para todos os gêneros e idades, com forte apelo para os aparatos tecnológicos, decorativos e automotivos. #dicas #ainfluenciadascores #interiordesign #fashiondesign #intersecçoes #alemdasformas #alemdaestetica

text:
walau sekarang kevin telah mendapatkan pekerjaan yang sangat cocok dan dapat membawa manfaat untuk dirinya dan orang banyak, kevin juga pernah mendapatkan diskriminasi saat melamar pekerjaan. pada masa transisinya, kevin pernah melamar ke salah satu perusahaan namun ditolak dengan alasan menjaga citra perusahaan, yakni dengan tidak merekrut karyawan transgender.  diskriminasi semacam inilah yang membuat teman-teman transgender sulit mendapatkan pekerjaan di sektor formal. diskriminasi ini juga berpengaruh terhadap berkembangnya stigma yang selalu melekatkan kata transgender dan pekerja seks (ps). meski tentu berbeda ceritanya jika seseorang memilih menjadi ps atas dasar keinginan pribadi mereka. kevin menyayangkan jika menjadi ps adalah satu-satunya pilihan yang dimiliki teman-teman transgender untuk bertahan hidup, sehingga harus menjalaninya dengan keterpaksaan.

text:
#mccover
噹噹噹，時髦如你，一定知道誰是 #文青女神 #lea ，@marieclairetw 這次難得在巴黎拍攝3月週年慶封面，跟lea相見歡。快來看看女神的簡介吧❤️❤️❤️
#leaseydoux #蕾雅瑟杜 在2013年的坎城影展出盡風頭，拿下金棕櫚獎的《#藍色是最溫暖的顏色》，為求導演致力追尋的真實性，她飾演的emma在冷酷節制的性格和女同志激情的爆發演出中得到平衡。姑且不論這部電影掀起的各種風波，奠定了她女演員的里程碑。________///
👉👉爾後，無論是好萊塢或歐陸藝術片，她嘗試各種可能，從《新美女與野獸》的貝拉公主、《布達佩斯大飯店》、到《巴黎聖羅蘭》《單身動物園》，和讓她拿下法國影后的《情慾凡爾賽》，輝煌的經歷讓她接下第七十一屆 #坎城影展 #festivalcannes  競賽單元評審。__________/// 👉👉不僅藝術片邀約不斷，導演們也看見了她骨子裡的毅力和大膽無畏的特質，邀約請出《不可能的任務4》的女殺手sabine和《007：惡魔四伏》裡面少見的、絕非花瓶的龐德女郎。__________/// 👉👉獅子座的她，有時候慵懶如貓，有時候堅決如獅。她看似柔媚溫馴，但肯定不是溫室裡的脆弱花兒，她疾呼好萊塢男女演員同酬，並挺身而出 #metoo ，主動投書《衛報》。她曾在專訪中提及：「我內心想到什麼，就會直接說出來，我不知道這該叫真誠，還是誠實，抑或是兩者，真誠的誠實。我沒有不計代價想要討好他人的意願，某種程度上來說，我喜歡追隨我自己。」 @leaseydoux_genuine leaseydoux_genuine @boucheron #boucheron #marieclairetw
hashtags: #mcCover, #文青女神, #Lea, #LeaSeydoux, #蕾雅瑟杜, #坎城影展, #festivalcannes, #MeToo, #boucheron, #marieclairetw

👉👉爾後，無論是好萊塢或歐陸藝術片，她嘗試各種可能，從《新美女與野獸》的貝拉公主、《布達佩斯大飯店》、到《巴黎聖羅蘭》《單身動物園》，和讓她拿下法國影后的《情慾凡爾賽》，輝煌的經歷讓她接下第七十一屆 #坎城影展 #festivalcannes  競賽單元評審。__________/// 👉👉不僅藝術片邀約不斷，導演們也看見了她骨子裡的毅力和大膽無畏的特質，邀約請出《不可能的任務4》的女殺手sabine和《007：惡魔四伏》裡面少見的、絕非花瓶的龐德女郎。__________/// 👉👉獅子座的她，有時候慵懶如貓，有時候堅決如獅。她看似柔媚溫馴，但肯定不是溫室裡的脆弱花兒，她疾呼好萊塢男女演員同酬，並挺身而出 #metoo ，主動投書《衛報》。她曾在專訪中提及：「我內心想到什麼，就會直接說出來，我不知道這該叫真誠，還是誠實，抑或是兩者，真誠的誠實。我沒有不計代價想要討好他人的意願，某種程度上來說，我喜歡追隨我自己。」 @leaseydoux_genuine leaseydoux_genuine @boucheron #boucheron #marieclairetw

噹噹噹，時髦如你，一定知道誰是 #文青女神 #lea ，@marieclairetw 這次難得在巴黎拍攝3月週年慶封面，跟lea相見歡。快來看看女神的簡介吧❤️❤️❤️
#leaseydoux #蕾雅瑟杜 在2013年的坎城影展出盡風頭，拿下金棕櫚獎的《#藍色是最溫暖的顏色》，為求導演致力追尋的真實性，她飾演的emma在冷酷節制的性格和女同志激情的爆發演出中得到平衡。姑且不論這部電影掀起的各種風波，奠定了她女演員的里程碑。________///
👉👉爾後，無論是好萊塢或歐陸藝術片，她嘗試各種可能，從《新美女與野獸》的貝拉公主、《布達佩斯大飯店》、到《巴黎聖羅蘭》《單身動物園》，和讓她拿下法國影后的《情慾凡爾賽》，輝煌的經歷讓她接下第七十一屆 #坎城影展 #festivalcannes  競賽單元評審。__________/// 👉👉不僅藝術片邀約不斷，導演們也看見了她骨子裡的毅力和大膽無畏的特質，邀約請出《不可能的任務4》的女殺手sabine和《007：惡魔四伏》裡面少見的、絕非花瓶的龐德女郎。__________/// 👉👉獅子座的她，有時候慵懶如貓，有時候堅決如獅。她看似柔媚溫馴，但肯定不是溫室裡的脆弱花兒，她疾呼好萊塢男女演員同酬，並挺身而出 #metoo ，主動投書《衛報》。她曾在專訪中提及：「我內心想到什麼，就會直接說出來，我不知道這該叫真誠，還是誠實，抑或是兩者，真誠的誠實。我沒有不計代價想要討好他人的意願，某種程度上來說，我喜歡追隨我自己。」 @leaseydoux_genuine leaseydoux_genuine @boucheron #boucheron #marieclairetw
＊
◤léa on the cover of marie claire taiwan  march 2019👸🏼◢
＊

stop_filter_tweet: 💋 ━･･━･･━･･━･･━･･━･･━ arieclairetw ━･･━･･━･･━･･━･･━･･━ ccover 噹噹噹，時髦如你，一定知道誰是 ， 這次難得在巴黎拍攝3月週年慶封面，跟lea相見歡。快來看看女神的簡介吧❤️❤️❤️ 在2013年的坎城影展出盡風頭，拿下金棕櫚獎的《色是最溫暖的顏色》，為求導演致力追尋的真實性，她飾演的emma在冷酷節制的性格和女同志激情的爆發演出中得到平衡。姑且不論這部電影掀起的各種風波，奠定了她女演員的里程碑。________/// 👉👉爾後，無論是好萊塢或歐陸藝術片，她嘗試各種可能，從《新美女與野獸》的貝拉公主、《布達佩斯大飯店》、到《巴黎聖羅蘭》《單身動物園》，和讓她拿下法國影后的《情慾凡爾賽》，輝煌的經歷讓她接下第七十一屆 競賽單元評審。__________/// 👉👉不僅藝術片邀約不斷，導演們也看見了她骨子裡的毅力和大膽無畏的特質，邀約請出《不可能的任務4》的女殺手sabine和《007：惡魔四伏》裡面少見的、絕非花瓶的龐德女郎。__________/// 👉👉獅子座的她，有時候慵懶如貓，有時候堅決如獅。她看似柔媚溫馴，但肯定不是溫室裡的脆弱花兒，她疾呼好萊塢男女演員同酬，並挺身而出 ，主動投書《衛報》。她曾在專訪中提及：「我內心想到什麼，就會直接說出來，我不知道這該叫真誠，還是誠實，抑或是兩者，真誠的誠實。我沒有不計代價想要討好他人的意願，某種程度上來說，我喜歡追隨我自己。」 leaseydoux_genuine arieclairetw ＊ ◤léa cover marie claire taiwan march 2019👸🏼◢ ＊

text:
“little mermaid" is far more tragic than the story of ariel that has since left an indelible mark on popular culture. she is motivated not only by her attraction to a prince, but the eternal soul that humans possess and mermaids do not. with the help of a sea witch, she trades her voice for legs. .
.
the mermaid must obtain true love's first kiss or the deal will result in her death. she attempts to enchant the prince with her dancing, despite the fact that it feels as though she is stepping on knives. he marries the human princess, whom he thinks saved him from a ship wreck (though, the little mermaid is truly the one responsible for his rescue). she is given the option to murder him in exchange for becoming a mermaid again. .
.
"in the end," as clements put it, "she loses the prince and she turns into sea foam."
.
.
moral of the story - be way more smarter than ariel..
.

another beautiful sculpture from @museelouvre 🌹 i feel the need to clarify something after an influx of inappropriate dm’s lately: my love of lingerie has nothing to do with gaining male attention or validation. it’s not shared as an invitation for lewd invitations or comments. it stems from a place of beauty, expressing femininity, creative structure. i’ve spent many years at war with my body, lingerie opens up a new and deep creativity, a place of comfort and artistic nature. i’m hoping to switch to a degree in fashion design this year as that’s where my passion truly lies, not in psychology. it’s taken a lot of hard work and soul searching to get to where i am now, that’s not something i’m going to risk being diminished by others thinking it appropriate to comment on my body in a sexual manor. this is an issue myself and fellow members of the lingerie addict community have to face; it’s bound to make us a target for this behaviour but that doesn’t mean it’s acceptable. 🌹#louvre #louvremuseum #museedulouvre #art #instaart #instaphotography #lingerieaddict #edrecovery #anorexiarecovery #metoo

text:
♀️♡intersectionality: the overlapping of discrimination everywhere.
♀️♡ableism: discrimination in favour able-bodied people. ♀️♡tone policing: focusing on the tone of the message delivered rather than the actual message. ♀️♡derailing: attempting to deflect criticism by redirecting the conversation to another issue. ♀️♡white feminism: focusing on the struggles faced by white women without addressing the oppression face by poc, ethnic minorities and women lacking other privileges. ♀️♡cultural appropriation: the unacknowledged/ inappropriate adoption of the customs, practices, ideas etc. of one people/society by a typically more dominant people/society.
♀️♡checking privileges: (it's in the name, but) reminding others/remembering that you are speaking from a privileged position.
name: Intersectional Feminist 🌻

text:
a great article from @iamwellandgood about addiction and how there is no black and white, it's all shades of grey. 
there is no need to wait for a terrible rock bottom but it seems most people today wait for a pretty devastating one rather than get help earlier in the progression of the issue. the stigma attached to alcoholics and substance abuse prevents people from being open and honest about it and only 1 in 10 people currently even seek help. often we are in denial about the issue, it's so shameful and isolating that we avoid sobriety at all costs. 
i entered treatment before i lost everything and i am so thankful. i have been open about it from day one because i saw my brother do it. i saw him being treated poorly for being sober and it infuriated me, he deserved support and cheers but he was able to let it go. i am fighting for all people who are struggling with alcohol and drugs to be treated with compassion and empathy, like any other illness. currently my friends are scared to tell their employers and doctors the truth because they know they will be judged harshly. 
someone close to me is struggling but they never had the strength to be honest and get help so they recently were let go, fired after 8 years 😥 it easily could have been me, i was on a downward spiral but thankfully caught myself and saved my life. i would have been devastated to lose the career i have worked so hard for. 
i have the book mentioned in the article and would recommend  the book "almost alcoholic ", it helped me enormously understand that addiction isn't black and white and we can change very very quickly from a social or moderate drinker to a dangerous drinker. stress is unpredictable and when my stress level increased, my drinking did as well and eventually things fell apart. 
don't wait to get help!

#drydiet #sober #nohangover #noalcohol #metoo #transformation #empoweringwomen #addictionrecovery #onedayatatime #soberaf #liveyourtruth #soberyogi

text:
i've watched the qspiracy since day one.

steve bannon left the wh august 2017 and q appeared the following october. do you believe in coincidences? 'j-c' church militant, anyone?

abusing and leaking presidential information to mislead the people and benefit a hijacked party is just business as usual.

however - while doing this djt, with the goonsquad known as gop, has willingly opened a pussy wound that anyone around the world can contaminate. i like to call it meddlin' with presidental blessin'. i'm not the only one who knows this and messes with the boombastic patriots - may be russia or china or mbs or antifa or me me me, a tiny quarter pounder sitting on me me me bed. obviously someone has a lot to lose when none of the us intelligence agencies ends this loonatic travesty.

qshow seems like a vile roleplay but instead it has become the heart of the propaganda operation that goebbels would have died for. it is clear that stuff like pizzagate™ was testing and groundwork for the 2016 election and since it proved to be very effective it is used still.

the accompanying memes go way beyond the propaganda of nsdap. social media companies are useless with the content - no way they are going to risk their business by taking responsibility.

there is no way that gop isn't aware of this - after all, cambridge analytica worked for ted cruz and john bolton. the whole narrative is built on the same facebook user data that bannon and the mercers reportedly got as cambridge analytica. pedofiles - i bet - but the way things are bundled sure makes goebbels shiver.

trump plays along with his tweets, gestures and words. the bigger issue still - the republicans willingly piggybacked this before the midterms and still keep abusing the faith of their fellow men.

this is not just an insane national security risk - it's a leaking conspiracy and treason in plain sight.

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytica $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
venus and pluto come together today in a sweet connection and you can find lots written about a new level of romantic love, a new level of financial love. 
how about a new level of body love? 
lots of talk about safety and safe relationships these days-  could you feel and see safety in your body just the way she is?

what if all of her imperfections, all the soft spots that should be hard the hard spots that should be perkier all the things your eyes go to first in the mirror were just as they should be? 
what if she, your body, really just needed to feel embraced and safe just the way she is?

text:
i recently had the incredible honour of joining the board of the dandelion initiative, a grassroots, not for profit organization, led by survivors, for survivors.

we believe in the power of education as a form of resistance to sexual violence.  survivors are not just victims, we are knowledgeable, skilled, resilient, informed, engaged, active and empowered.

there are three main ways you can support our work and survivors:

1. sign up your establishment for the safer bars + spaces training. this is a 3.5hrs course which utilizes an intersectional and trauma-informed framework, applying survivor centric practices to create safer spaces that can recognize, prevent and respond to sexual harassment and violence. 
2. hire the dandelion initiative to write your anti-harassment/anti-sexual violence workplace policies. in ontario all employers are required to have an anti-harassment and sexual violence policy in accordance to bill 132- the amendment made to the occupational health and safety act. hire us to help you build strong, clear, survivor centric and inclusive policies.
3. donate! we cannot continue to provide supports and advocate for survivors without funding, so click on the donate now button! 
@dandelioninitiative #webelievesurvivors #timesup #metoo #metoocannabis

text:
[#아시아경제 김흥순 기자] #체육계시민단체 가 #폭력 과 #성폭력 등으로 고통받는 우리 선수들의 #인권침해 문제를 근절하기 위해 #국제올림픽위원회(ioc)에 도움을 요청한다. 정부의 엘리트 체육 쇄신안에 반발하는 이기흥 회장을 비롯한 대한체육회에 대해 ioc 차원의 진상조사와 책임을 규명해 달라는 호소문을 전달할 방침이다.

#체육시민연대 와 #문화연대 , #스포츠문화연구소, #한국여성단체연합 등 8개 시민사회단체는 22일 #토마스바흐 #ioc 위원장 앞으로 이 같은 내용을 담은 서한을 보낼 예정이다. 
이경렬 체육시민연대 사무국장은 "외신(cnn)에서도 국내 빙상계에서 촉발된 '미투(#metoo · #나도당했다 )'에 대해 보도하고, 국제빙상경기연맹(isu)은 '이와 관련한 한국 당국의 철저한 조사와 사법부 판단을 지지한다'는 성명까지 냈지만 ioc는 아직까지 특별한 언급을 하지 않고 있어 편지를 보내게 됐다"고 설명했다.

시민단체들은 서한에서 "대한체육회가 '국가올림픽위원회(noc)는 정부의 개입으로부터 자유로워야한다'는 ioc 헌장을 근거로 사회적 이슈와 정부의 노력을 무력화하고 있다"며 "정부의 스포츠 혁신이 시작하기 전부터 거부하는 움직임을 보이고 있다"고 지적했다. ========================================== #체육계개혁 의 중심에서 통찰과 실행으로 
강렬한 울림을 전달 하는 연구소.
"지금까지 이런 연구소는 없었다.” 😭 🧐 🤫 =========================================== #스포츠문화포럼 #스포츠문화연구소세미나 
#스포츠시민단체 #깨어있는체육인
#체육계개혁의시작 #체육계개혁의움직임 #스포츠문화포럼 / 스포츠혁신의중심📍#스포츠문화연구소사무국장 #ㅅㅁㅅ사무국장⠀⠀⠀ ⠀ ⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀ ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

[ 김흥순 기자]  가  과  등으로 고통받는 우리 선수들의  문제를 근절하기 위해  도움을 요청한다. 정부의 엘리트 체육 쇄신안에 반발하는 이기흥 회장을 비롯한 대한체육회에 대해 ioc 차원의 진상조사와 책임을 규명해 달라는 호소문을 전달할 방침이다.

 와  ,   등 8개 시민사회단체는 22일   위원장 앞으로 이 같은 내용을 담은 서한을 보낼 예정이다. 
이경렬 체육시민연대 사무국장은 "외신(cnn)에서도 국내 빙상계에서 촉발된 '미투( ·  )'에 대해 보도하고, 국제빙상경기연맹(isu)은 '이와 관련한 한국 당국의 철저한 조사와 사법부 판단을 지지한다'는 성명까지 냈지만 ioc는 아직까지 특별한 언급을 하지 않고 있어 편지를 보내게 됐다"고 설명했다.

시민단체들은 서한에서 "대한체육회가 '국가올림픽위원회(noc)는 정부의 개입으로부터 자유로워야한다'는 ioc 헌장을 근거로 사회적 이슈와 정부의 노력을 무력화하고 있다"며 "정부의 스포츠 혁신이 시작하기 전부터 거부하는 움직임을 보이고 있다"고 지적했다. ==========================================  의 중심에서 통찰과 실행으로 
강렬한 울림을 전달 하는 연구소.
"지금까지 이런 연구소는 없었다.” 😭 🧐 🤫 ===========================================

text:
i’d like to describe myself as an intersectional feminist. social media has created an unfortunate stigma against feminism due to women using feminism as an excuse for radicalism. the first step that any woman or man has to take as a feminist is identifying exactly why you are a feminist and what type of a feminist you are. 
an intersectional feminist is a woman or a man who understands and supports the fact that sexism, racism, classism and other global oppressive matters are all intertwined with one another. we cannot start from anywhere but the bottom of the pyramid if we want to enact change as global citizens. intersectional feminism has helped me to go forth with my ambitions and my passion for women’s rights and politics as i have been able to ignore the misogyny that comes my way, in an unfortunately patriarchal country 
as a woman, i have a lot of anger due to the day to day problems that i encounter because i am female. i’ve always told myself to turn that anger into something positive and that is why i will continue to re-power women to rise above the oppression of the twenty-first century. no one can help us if we don’t help ourselves. we need to place ourselves on the same pedestal that men place themselves on and understand the importance of going forth as a human being before going forth based on our sex. women’s rights are human rights.

text:
二月書分享《#沒什麼事是喝一碗奶茶不能解決的》
作者 #梁瑜
#芭樂人類學 第一屆 #芭樂籽 首獎金芭樂作品
#四月小姐的讀後感
#我是四月
#為什麼不是五月

書的內容出於台灣原住民到中國北大人類學研究所與到新疆維族做田野研究時，觀察或體驗到的趣事與文化衝擊。

食物常為接觸異文化的開端，例如：到香港吃豬扒包、去越南啖河粉。我實在印象特別深刻書中提及的「大盤雞」，看作者描述如何製造時，邊看邊飢腸轆轆。曾谷歌新疆餐廳，只為了想找與敘述完美相襯的大盤雞，尤其是香麻湯汁、手打麵與土豆（馬鈴薯）的結合。

除了飲食外，對哈薩克人（是的，你沒看錯，維吾爾人包括哈薩克族）來說，「喝奶茶」是生活中最不可或缺的飲料與「活動」之一了。手搖飲料店對台灣人說是不可或缺的存在，那對哈薩克人來說，「喝茶」也是。但我覺得「喝」的當下與場景有著十萬八千里的落差。一杯五十嵐是我們在做某件事的附屬品，喝一杯奶茶卻對他們有參雜時間的概念。例如：「約幾點？」、「下午喝完茶後吧」。當然，更重要的是：遠方的客人與家人相聚在一起，喝茶前做了什麼、喝茶後要做什麼，喝茶時坐哪裡、誰負責倒茶，都是有根據的。

非常認同作者所說：「唯有將自己縮得很小很小，才有可能獲得更大的空間。」（i have to forget who i am）生活與旅遊不同，作者在書的最後提及生活在北京、生活在新疆，喜怒哀樂與自身認同混雜的日子；並感性地自審生活的土地、來自的國家；溫柔地同理與自己不同文化的人。 *註：漢人與維族人不同，可以進一步了解現在正在「新疆」文化、信仰上發生的悲歌，已經不是喝碗奶茶能夠解決的。
#東突厥斯坦 #eastturkistan #uygur #再教育營 #reeducationalcamp #metoo *圖二：至香港轉機時，香港媒體報導土耳其政府譴責中共的再教育營

text:
parents, what do you know about kik? probably nothing! why? because it's one of those messaging apps that is primarily marketed to kids. so, here's what you need to know....
kik is a messaging app that allows users to communicate anonymously. enter an email address (it isn't  verified, so it can be fake) and create a user name and you're ready to go on kik. no need to reveal your name, phone number or age. 
thus, kik users have the freedom to post without the concern for reprisals. not surprisingly, this feeling of freedom has emboldened bullies and allowed child predators to prey on children through the app. 
additionally, kik has more functionality than your typical social messaging platform. kik can be used to access the web, create videos, listen to music, and create memes. kik does not store or have access to view the messages exchanged between users, which makes tracing a bully or an online predator's interaction with a child impossible. predators can literally create a fake email address and make up a user name every day to stay undetected by the app's administrators and law enforcement if they so desire. 
the lack of vetting and the knowledge that there is no way to trace the messages back to them also allows predators to be very aggressive in propositioning minors. 
for parents who are unfamiliar with the site, kik does have a safety center for you to learn about the app's functionalities. and, as we've said repeatedly, parents should take every opportunity to learn the particulars of the various social media apps that are being used by kids these days. this basic knowledge will allow you to speak with your children from a place of understanding and help them  use the apps in a safe, positive and responsible manner. #childsexabuseawareness #stopchildsexabuse #childsexabusesurvivor #parentsofchilldsexabusesurvivor #sexualassault #endchildsexabuse #endrapeculture #childabuse #sextrafficking #atlanta #atl #georgia #women #girls #teens #awareness #rapevictim #victim #children #prevention #trafficking  #survivor #tips #blogger #speaker #metoo #advocate #volunteer #activist #super bowl

text:
it always feels so good when readers love my books and let others know - and even more when they see a need for my books, when they know my books can help others feel less alone, stop hurting themselves, know they are strong, and heal. books are such a safe and powerful way to explore painful issues and be reminded of our own strength. 
so i was delighted when reader linda hall-webster posted this. thank you for your generosity, linda, in buying a copy for your library, too! you are a sweetheart. 
from linda hall-webster: "one of my favorites! found it in the wild and had to grab it - cheryl rainfield, i knew i’d find one . ❤

this is actually my second copy purchased for myself. the first i donated to the library i used to work at because i knew it needed to be there. ❤ 
this work resonates with me for various reasons, mainly it’s a great story of over coming strife, leaning to trust not only yourself, your thoughts and memories too and that over all love is stronger than anything." #cherylrainfield #yawriter #lgbtqwriter #booknerd #bookworm #ireadya #survivor #feminist #yalit #yabooks #bookstagram #bookrecs #scars #hunted #stained #selfharm #selfinjury #cutting #sexualabuse #trauma #healing #metoo #csa #sexualassault
#loveisstronger #lovewins #lovetrumpshate #lgbtqya #lgbtqia

text:
“i was a nuclear site guard. my colleagues sexually assaulted me.” this is yet another tale of assault and ongoing harassment - this time, at a national security site. another tale of a woman who did everything she was supposed to do by reporting it up the chain of command, along with witnesses. the torment continued and then the retaliation began. she was subjected to psychological exams and eventually fired. ⠀⠀
. . .⠀⠀
yes, egregious behavior still happens on the job every day. and no, this is not the story of a few "bad actors." the system is fundamentally flawed and completely broken. it's time for a revolution, hr.⠀⠀
. . . ⠀⠀

text:
if you read anything i post, please let it be this. ⁣
⁣
the other day an incident occurred at work where a man exposed himself to me in my office. afterwards, i sat there racking my brain for what i did to give him the impression that his behavior was okay. i was completely blown away as this had never happened to me before. as i processed the incident with another clinician, i thought, was it the scent of my lotion, perfume, fabric softener, shampoo, body wash? these fellas can pick up any scent that doesn’t smell like testosterone. was i dressed up to much or my makeup overdone? keep in mind, i go to work every day looking like a hamster because i want to attract the least amount of attention (if you want to know what a human hamster looks like, watch my weekday videos). maybe it was my lamps? do my lamps create an inviting environment for sexual behavior? i had recently brought lamps with warm lighting into my office because the overhead fluorescent lights were killing my eyes and i felt lamps created a welcoming environment for “therapy.”⁣
⁣
i made it to lamps before my coworker shut down my processing. she brought to my awareness the fact i was sitting there looking for what i had done wrong to be treated that way. i was taking the blame away from the male and placing it on myself. that’s what’s wrong with society today. we search for what we did wrong to give the impression it’s okay to be treated this way. ⁣
⁣
the reason i share this with you is that given all i know about human behavior, i fell victim to this thinking. to make sense of what happened, i was placing blame on myself and taking it away from the person who did the act. i realize now, he made a choice, and there is nothing i did that makes his behavior acceptable. ⁣
⁣
ladies, please know sexual harassment is not acceptable just because you have boobs and a butt. being female doesn’t come with a sign on your back that says “treat me like your sex object.” if you ever fall victim to sexual harassment do not look for what you did wrong that gave off the impression it was okay to be treated that way. if you have fallen victim to harassment or abuse please seek help from a professional therapist.⁣

text:
1. $15 minimum wage would destroy small business. 
2. we have devastating government spending as it is. plus making people more dependent on the government is terrible.
3. the green new deal plans to ban cars and planes. it’s aoc ridiculous first try at being productive.
4. i’m down for prison reform.
5. it’s not the governments job to pay for your bullshit major in something you’ll never get a job in. i’m paying out of pocket for school. it’s rough but it’s possible.
6. universal background checks are already a thing. automatics have been banned since the 80s i don’t know what you mean by ban assault rifles.
7. do you mean like fix broken down abandoned buildings? that’s stupid they’ll just fall into the same condition because no one will take care of it.
8. pull them out we don’t need to be in shit countries full of backwards civilizations.

11. why?

13. unions work where unions are needed.

15. if you work and have insurance it’s really not a problem.
16. that’s between a person and their employer. not the government.
17. award people for breaking the law that sounds great.
18. that’s stupid. if someone wants to donate to an election let them.
19. wage gap is a myth.
20. they already have equality.
thanks for coming to my ted talk if you actually read all that.

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green
devil's bargain: steve bannon, donald trump, and the storming of the presidency

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green

text:
this was a serious business, it was actually backed by goldman sachs, but it crashed and went bankrupt because the gamers themselves who weren't cheating became enraged basically that these other people were doing, they put so much pressure on the gaming companies.

they put so much pressure on the video game companies, that they decided to basically ban gold-farming, which killed bannon's business, but it awakened him to the power of what he called "rootless white males" who spend all their time online. and five years later when bannon wound up at breitbart, he resolved to try and attract those people over to breitbart because he thought they could be radicalized in a kind of populist, nationalist way. and the way that bannon did that, the bridge between the angry abusive gamers and breitbart and pepe was milo yiannopoulous, who bannon discovered and hired to be breitbart's tech editor.

from the time i met him in 2011, he's had exactly the same politics. the same stuff you heard from trump, you saw on the campaign trail. what he was looking for was a vessel because nobody in republican washington believed in these kinds of ideas. the whole trend in the republican party was toward liberalizing immigration laws, passing comprehensive immigration reform. he was against it.

joshua green

text:
former u.s. national security adviser michael flynn admitted on friday that he asked russia to delay a u.n. vote seen as damaging to israel, but diplomats said it was not the only country he and presidential adviser jared kushner lobbied.

in the hours before the vote by the 15-member united nations security council on dec. 23, flynn also phoned the u.n. missions of uruguay and malaysia, and kushner spoke with kim darroch, the british ambassador to the united states, according to diplomats familiar with the conversations, who spoke on condition of anonymity.

the lobbying took place before republican president donald trump, who was known for his pro-israel campaign rhetoric, took office on jan. 20. it failed, with the security council adopting a resolution demanding an end to israeli settlement building on land palestinians want for an independent state. the vote was 14 in favor and one abstention by the united states.

the efforts made on israel's behalf capped several days of unusual diplomacy. in a surprise dec. 21 move, egypt had called for a vote the next day on the draft resolution, prompting both trump and israel to urge washington to veto the text.

a senior israeli official told reuters that israeli officials contacted trump's transition team at a "high level" to ask for help after failing to persuade democratic president barack obama's administration to veto the draft u.n. resolution.

according to court documents made public on friday, a member of trump's presidential transition team, later identified by sources as trump's son-in-law kushner, told flynn on dec. 22 to contact officials from foreign governments, including russia, to convince them to delay the vote or veto the resolution.

flynn spoke with then-russian ambassador to the united states sergei kislyak that day, and again the following day, according to the court documents.

michelle nichols
reuters

text:
- this was steve bannon's baby, said former contractor christopher wylie, who described cambridge analytica as "bannon's arsenal of weaponry to wage a culture war on america using military strategies."
.
bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

text:
alexandra waterbury’s world exploded after she filed a lawsuit in september against new york city ballet and her ex-boyfriend chase finlay, a former principal dancer with the company. doing so made waterbury the only dancer to publicly come forward and to use her name in what has since become a major part of the ballet world’s #metoo reckoning.⁣
⁣
a one-time elite student at the school of american ballet (new york city ballet’s affiliate academy), waterbury practically lived at lincoln center, dancing up to 36 hours a week and graduating with an offer to turn pro with the washington ballet. today her professional dance career is over.⁣
⁣
@alexandra_waterbury now has her sights on an ivy league degree and a modeling career. still, she warns future ballerinas of dance’s perils. read more at the link in our bio. (🖊: @rainesfordalexandra, 📸: @heathersten)⁣

imagine that. 
#metoo will always be relevant

text:
det er fredag dere, og jeg prøver å komme i gang med noe av det jeg liker aller mest, nemlig å skrive. akkurat nå skjer det så mye i livet mitt at jeg har problemer med å henge med i svingene. instagram har jeg måttet nedprioritere, og dagene mine går med til kurs, jobbing, trening, og å planlegge vårens mange oppgaver som trener. forandringene ligger der på rekke og rad, og jeg skal ta vare på meg selv og dem jeg er glad i underveis. jeg har alltid ment at jeg selv har ansvaret for å skape de endringene i livet, som gir meg bedre livskvalitet, og fremgang. akkurat dette er ingen selvfølge, dersom jeg går rundt med et selvbilde hvor jeg ofte kjenner på at jeg ikke fortjener å lykkes. for litt siden skrev en venn av meg disse vakre ordene på sin facebook profil: «døden er intet. det er livet som er. den virkelige død er den du dør hver dag du ikke lever». ordene traff meg mitt i hjertet, og med dem ble mine egne drømmer og mål forsterket. ikke sett livet på vent. la oss alle leve livet mens vi er her. våg å sanse, føle, leve, og elske med hele hjertet. ikke se på deg selv som en raring dersom du er et menneske som føler mye... det å kunne leve mer i dybden av livet, er en gave ikke alle evner å sette pris på. å være et følelsesmenneske koster en del, men  gir også mye glede. det å kjenne sterkere på følelser, fange opp signaler og stemninger, lese andre mennesker, opplever jeg i dag som en berikelse, men som jentunge var det vondt... er du et følelsesmenneske?
.
sjekk storyen og sveip for flere bilder 👀

text:
😭i was utterly and completely overwhelmed by the outpouring of "we've been there too"s that y'all so graciously shared in response to my latest post about having to rehome @ruthietherescue.
*
by making that post i knew it would make her not being with us even more real, but what i didn't realize is the shame i had about the situation😔. i felt like we failed her. i felt like i was a bad dog mom and that i just wasn't enough. i was afraid of any judgment or frankly even questions from well-meaning folks that i would likely only interpret as "did you really try hard, did you really do enough?". and you know what? none of those questions came (at least not yet). instead, i've been overwhelmed by the amount of kind hearts❤️ that have been through the same situation and are on the other side of it saying "it's going to be okay. it's hard but you did make the right decision and you did do your best. and it gets better".
*
and you know what else came out of this whole sharing situation? a reminder about shame. a reminder that shame can't exist in the light- when your fears and hurts are shuffled out of the darkness into the light, you can see them for what they really are and if you're really lucky, you have people in your corner to let you know your best is enough and it's all going to be okay. shame is an ugly irrational voice that creeps up in my head and heart more than i'd care to admit. and if it's not shame, it's a high-level defensiveness that is lightning fast quick to anticipate and have a response ready to explain my actions. when will i let that go?!
*
i've decided to start a #shedyourshame series where i plan on sharing things about myself that either bring up shame or that lightning fast defensiveness i'm so so good at. i know this will help me work through a few things, but my hope is that it helps you too. let's link arms and remind each other that we've been there too- whatever there is. #shame #metoo #brenebrown
*
*
*
*

.
.
.
.
.
.

next stop...best sellers list. yall i need your support to spread the word about this. 
at the moment it's just me doing marketing and i have no clue how to market. word of mouth is the best so i'm asking genuinely if this story has touched yu in any way, please share the word. my goal is to get this to a million people but i know i cant do this alone.

who do you know that needs to hear a story about resilience, redemption, love and forgiveness? 
6 degree of separation before this spreads globally!

text: flashbacks to yesterday’s remarkably freeing and meditative two-hour early morning exploration of the beach 🌊. i was strongly moved to try my first instagram live — video shown here. as a social media coach and consultant, i’ve helped launch many live moments for others but never for myself. yesterday and more importantly over the last few days, i have started to find my voice again. travel karen, as close friends refer to me, is re-emerging as the free-spirited woman that has faced a multitude of fears in her past including surviving and thriving after more health crises that i can count (three major ones just this past year alone) and other tougher life moments. i forget that i am a fighter and a thriver —a woman who lives by my father's favorite saying ✨'what you gave you will always have what you didn't you lost forever."✨ i share this not to boast but show anything is possible when you let go and let the love around you carry you to new opportunities. to date, i have explored more than 15 countries (some alone) and more cities and experiences than i can count. i tend to forget the amazing things i have accomplished for myself personally, professionally and spiritually—from sunrise walks around the streets of chang mai following the monks, climbing up to machu picchu after surviving an early breast cancer scare, superwoman (no hands and upside down) zip lining after surviving yet another major endometriosis surgery, going back to school at 40 to change careers and starting over, being a full-time caregiver to my parents for months on end on the ground and behind the scenes for more than 15 years, to getting up the courage to go on live international tv at a moment's notice ... to cherishing holding hands and walking the streets of brooklyn with my love or laying under the stars with friends basking in the beauty of our world. i share this as a reminder of our remarkable existence, even when life is tougher. we are here for a bigger reason. since my words helped another woman i learned this morning, another survivor, i will continue to share of myself. my strength and voice. it’s an odd place for me but also an exhilarating one. onward. gratitude. ♥️

text:
i have found my healing process to be so much smoother and more enjoyable when i reframe identifying statements from negative to positive. as an incest and illness survivor, i have felt behind my peers as i’ve had to devote so much time to recovery, i’ve felt lost as i’ve pioneered my own recovery process, i’ve felt sick as i’ve been surrounded by wellness, i’ve felt confused as i’ve tried to redefine my life, i’ve felt lonely as i walked away from an abusive community, i’ve felt anxious as i’ve doubted myself every step of the way, i’ve felt tired from managing recovery and life responsibilities, i’ve felt damaged as i’ve picked up the pieces of my experience, and i’ve felt unrooted as i uprooted myself to find a new home. it hasn’t been until recently that i’ve learned to reframe this narrative of loss and loneliness into a positive: i have the opportunity now to learn so much, to explore new worlds, to recover into who i want to be, to create a new life for myself, to connect to new loving people, to grow safely and proudly, to rest when i need to, to heal into wholeness, and to build a new identity upon a foundation of love. how can you reframe disparaging thoughts into ones that inspire you to heal, to find home, and to hold yourself more lovingly?
.
.
.
#metoo #recovery #timesup #icantkeepquiet #women #selfcare #care #help #healing #hope #happiness #gentleness #reframe

text:
do you know what happens when a child reports sexual abuse?
✨
we hear a lot in the media about getting organizations to report abuse, mandatory reporters to report, adults to report, and children to tell if they’re being hurt. what we don’t hear is what happens in reality when a report is made.
✨
a study was done in south carolina to look at how child abuse was handled in that state and to see how they could improve their services. the report showed the following
•
➡️ when professionals were asked the percentage of child sexual abuse cases that actually go to a criminal trial, the majority of the responses said 0-15%.
➡️ when asked how many child sexual abuse cases go to trial in family court the reponse was similar 0-15%.
➡️ they estimated that only 55% of child sexual abuse reports got investigated.
➡️ when asked why professionals don’t report their suspicions of child abuse they said many have stopped reporting because nothing happens when they do.
•
this is not south carolina’s problem. this happens in every state. nationally it is estimated that only 25% of named abusers even get arrested - let alone prosecuted or convicted.
✨
we can’t claim that it is an adult’s responsibility to protect children when nothing happens when they try to do just that. we can’t tell children to come forward when nothing happens if they do.
✨
something does happen though - a child is betrayed by those that were supposed to protect them, and they may feel like a liar or feel guilt or shame because they didn’t do the right thing to be believed. and an abuser is vindicated and empowered.
✨
we have to face the reality of what happens when a child does report, and we can’t let them down when they do. we must have a system that believes, protects, and defends the first child the first time they say their abuser’s name. 💞
•
read sarah’s speech at the link in the bio ➡️ who will you choose to empower to see what happens to a child when they report abuse.
✨
i wrote a blog about the 3 things i want parents to know. you can read it at the link in the bio ➡️ one year later, what parents need to know
#empowerchildren #defendsurvivors  #csa #mandatoryreporter #believeprotectdefend

text:
hi, my name is roxanne darling (@roxannedarling) and this is my week to takeover instagram from the los angeles center of photography (lacp) @la_centerofphoto. i am an emerging artist currently living in santa fe, nm. i love that lacp welcomes out-of-state photographers to be part of their community. this week, let's talk about bodies, nature, and getting older!

image: 
i am: going toe to toe with my shadow

the photos i’m sharing this week are of me, from my series of portraits in nature. as a 66-year-old woman and emerging artist, i’m exploring the:
* the natural desire to be unclothed outdoors, in the privacy of precious places;
* a newly discovered quality of self-acceptance for my aging self;
* an appetite to create art from the female gaze, as a type of reclaiming my time, my body, and my point of view.

text: it's noah break up day! or at least that event is on my mind. i honestly don't remember the exact date, just that it was before my moms birthday which is the 25th. i'm doing well over all, just annoyed looking back on the entire relationship and how it started. he wanted a bj. the entire fucking mess has been over something so trivial, and fleeting. ten minutes of pleasure turned into ten years of lies, pointless bickering, cyber stalking, lawyers and law enforcement. i didn't want that while he was sleeping around. all he had to do was call someone else. there were up to four girls he was entertaining at any given time. instead he created the entire ruse of a serious relationship with me. but i'm the weak one. i'm the coward. i'm the crazy one. ha! i mean really, all i can do is laugh at it so many years later. i’m only noting it in an effort to uncover some repressed trauma i’ve been struggling with in recent weeks, which is why i’ve been a little quiet around here lately. to read more about our relationship and how it impacted my life be sure to check out candy apple butterscotch available now on amazon or at the #linkinbio #authorsofinstagram #indieauthor #ptsdsurvivor #metoo #memoir #nonfiction #books #writingcommunity

text:
wylie said that bannon's plans began to solidify in 2014, when cambridge analytica consulted various republican campaigns and pacs ahead of the midterm elections. the company began to test and apply its psychographics by using facebook data to model individuals' personality types in order to understand how to influence them.

documents show the john bolton super pac, which promoted candidates supported by recently appointed white house national security adviser john bolton, paid cambridge analytica $454,700 in 2014 for "behavioral microtargeting with psychographic messaging." those services included strategies that broke individual voters into "clusters" based on what messages would resonate with them.

wylie also said the company used focus groups and messaging trials in 2014 to test some of the concepts that became core themes of the trump campaign, such as "drain the swamp" and imagery of walls. "a lot of the narratives of the trump campaign were what we were testing in 2014," wylie said.

he added that bannon directly presided over much of the company's initial research. "everything that we were doing ultimately had to be passed up to bannon for approval," said wylie, who left the company in late 2014.

wylie said bannon would fly to london about once a month for company meetings, and during that time he came to understand bannon's ideology. "he really liked the idea of using a military-style approach to changing people's perceptions," wylie said.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan & drew griffin
cnn

text:
christopher wylie, the whistleblower who exposed the widespread misuse of data by his former employer, cambridge analytica, has revealed how the company “weaponised” the fashion industry in the run up to the 2016 us election, which he claims helped donald trump get elected.

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for particular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in particular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser reported “weapons of mass destruction”.
.
- they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with certain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a particular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what reports often call “populist political signalling”.
.
cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political advertising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

speaking at the annual bof voices festival in oxfordshire, wylie revealed for the first time a matrix based on data collected by the firm which he claims can show how users’ preferences for paicular brands on social media platforms – facebook, in paicular – were then used to help target these same users with pro-trump messaging. he compared the misuse of fashion-based data as one of the campaign’s lesser repoed “weapons of mass destruction”.
.
- they [cambridge analytica] looked at actual people. how they engaged with ceain brands was put into a funnel and helped build the algorithms, wylie explained. - when you look at personality traits, music and fashion are the most informative [tools] for predicting someone’s personality. a user’s predilection for a paicular label gives, he said, a very clear indication of what repos often call “populist political signalling”.
.
cambridge analytica, which was shut down earlier this year following an investigation by the observer, was the political marketing firm headed by trump’s former key adviser, steve bannon, and owned by hedge-fund billionaire robe mercer. it also used user information obtained without authorisation in early 2014 – including cultural preferences such as fashion and music – to create a system that could single out voters in order to expose them to specific political adveising.

morwenna ferrier
the guardian

text:
according to the times, cambridge analytica bought the data from aleksandr kogan, a russian-american academic. kogan, who told facebook he was conducting academic research, built a facebook personality quiz app called "thisisyourdigitalife." when users downloaded the app, it scraped all of their available facebook data, including their friends, their likes and where they lived.

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer".
.
in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field."
.
despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

more than a quarter-million facebook users downloaded the app, which also exploited a facebook vulnerability that allowed it to to collect most of the same data from the friends of those who downloaded it. by prying into the friends lists of those who made the download, kogan was able to get data from more than 50 million people.

throughout 2015 and into 2016, the cruz campaign paid cambridge analytica almost $6 million for data that the campaign used for what it called "psychographic targeting," which supposedly allowed the campaign to tailor its message to specific voters in places like iowa and new hampshire, where single voters can make a big difference. using data from the firm, the campaign built profiles of potential voters, prioritizing those who fit in categories such as "stoic traditionalist" and "true believer".
.
in december 2015, the same month the guardian revealed cambridge analytica and kogan's data harvesting practices, cruz campaign spokesman rick tyler called the company a "market leader and the best in the field."
.
despite tyler's claim that the cruz campaign stopped using the firm's data in early 2016, it kept paying cambridge analytica until june of that year, a month after cruz suspended his campaign. after cruz dropped out of the race, the firm began working with trump, supporting him through november's general election against hillary clinton.

stephen young
dallas observer

text:
wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

bannon worked on trump's campaign and became a white house aide when trump took office in january 2017. bannon left in august 2017.

wylie, who has provided reports about how the firm used data facebook collected, on wednesday described discussions at the company about suppressing the vote, exploiting racial tensions, and testing campaign slogans in 2014 for use in the 2016 election.
.
- one of the things that did provoke me to leave was the beginnings of discussions of voter disengagement, i have seen documents reference and i recall conversations that it was intended to focus on african-american voters, wylie said. - the company learned that there were segments of the population that responded to messages like 'drain the swamp' or images of border walls or indeed paranoia about the 'deep state' that weren't necessarily reflected in mainstream polling or mainstream political discourse that steve bannon was interested in to help build his movement, wylie said.

another witness who testified to the judiciary committee, tufts university associate professor eitan hersh, said he was "skeptical" of the effectiveness that such political messaging and targeting. - no person is persuadable all the time, he said.

mark hosenball
reuters

text:
u.s. president donald trump's former aide steve bannon sought to use personal information collected online to promote "a culture war," a whistleblower on now-defunct political data firm cambridge analytica told u.s. senators on wednesday.

bannon, a former cambridge analytica vice president, "saw cultural warfare as a means to create enduring change in american politics," testified christopher wylie, who says information about tens of millions of facebook users ended up in cambridge analytica's hands.

bannon's attorney william burck did not immediately respond to an email request for comment on wylie's testimony.

wylie, who worked for scl, the british-based parent of cambridge analytica, told the senate judiciary committee that cambridge analytica hired hackers to collect data it then used against opponents of its political clients.

allegations of the improper use of data for 87 million facebook users by cambridge analytica, which was hired by trump's 2016 election campaign, have led to investigations in the united states and europe.

mark hosenball
reuters
