bannon wanted to use the sorts of aggressive messaging tactics usually reserved for geopolitical conflicts to move the us electorate further to the right, wylie said. he had already directed a series of anti-establishment, conservative documentary films and presided over the far-right website breitbart news, but cambridge analytica would mark another step in his overall ambitions to transform the nation.

with financial backing from hedge-fund billionaire robert mercer, bannon co-founded cambridge analytica in 2013 as the us-branch of strategic communication laboratories (scl) group, a british company that advertises how it has conducted "behavioral change" programs in more than 60 countries.

wylie described cambridge analytica as - steve bannon and robert mercer using a foreign, military contractor ... to use some of the same techniques that the military uses ... on the american electorate.

curt devine, donie o'sullivan and drew griffin
cnn

•
selain bentuk-bentuk kekerasan seksual diatas, juga terdapat fakta lain bahwa terdapat hambatan dan kesulitan melaporkan tindak kekerasan seksual yang dialami oleh laki-laki, karena di masyarakat kita sudah terbangun tuntutan standar bahwa laki-laki itu kuat, macho, pemimpin dsb. •

standarisasi tersebut justru menyebabkan laki-laki merasa malu dan khawatir untuk melaporkan tindak pelecehan seksual yang terjadi pada dirinya, karena masyarakat patriarkis akan mendakwanya sebagai “bukan laki-laki sejati” dengan pertanyaan-pertanyaan yang menyudutkan seperti “yang benar saja, masa laki-laki dilecehkan?”
•
dan reviktimasi korbanpun kembali terjadi. •

text:
certain people will fight tooth and nail for someone to be born, up until they end up being different.
the same people fighting to end abortion are the same who want noriam to be tortured, beaten, psychologically tormented, to commit suicide, or even killed for being queer and trans.
the same people fighting to end abortion laugh at migrant children seeking asylum dying, overlook authorities destroying life saving resources, and blame the parents.
the same people fighting to end abortion are the same ones who are against single parents recovering government assistance to take care of their kids.
the same people fighting to end abortion are the same ones who are against people with physical disabilities and invisible illnesses being views as functioning members of society and make jokes about them behind their back or flat out wish to exterminate, yes... “exterminate”... they’ve used that word, sickeningly... them from the world.
the same people fighting to end abortion are the same ones who refused to hold men accountable for sexually assaulting women and make excuses for victims to take the blame for their assault because of their wardrobe and activities in public spaces, then ignore their stories, threaten them for speaking out, and mock the movements meant for them to heal from their trauma and bring their abusers to justice.
it’s interesting how undervalued someone becomes once they turn out to be black or brown, ethnic, gay, transgender, disabled, non christian, or female. this is why the anti-choice movement is nothing more than hypocritical nonsense. if they aren’t willing to stand up for the preexisting lives of stigmatized and marginalized individuals, like noriam, a queer, transgender autistic individual, then it becomes extremely evident that their motives are performative and nothing more.
like and follow the activist parent - susan jordan on facebook for more!

text:
girls will be...a mother-daughter love story about a sexually curious teen and her anxious mom discover the value of trust and how to break the cycle.

residing in a fictional small, conservative town in indiana, annie wants to explore her sexuality. grace baxter wants to protect her daughter from the high-stakes that comes with being female. when annie's caught making out with her boyfriend, grace's past comes to the surface and the mother-daughter roller coaster begins. grace must reckon with her haunting memories of sex, abortion, and expectations of women prior to the #metoo movement, while annie gets answers for why her mom's such a tight-ass. after all, it's just sex...isn't it? #writingcommunity #womensupportwomen #womenempowerment #womenwriters #prochoice #metoo #sexeducation #reproductiverights #plannedparenthood #parenting #motherhood #opencommunication

text:
this workshop & support group is for women and men who need a safe space & support to heal from their experiences with sexual abuse. our main objective in this workshop series is to clear the psychological and energetic imprint that sexual trauma may have left on us that affects who we are and how we function in the world. it is so important and necessary that we reclaim our power over our sexuality and over our lives now and for generations to come, so that we may operate from a place of healing rather than a place of hurt. •

within this safe space, you will have the option to share your experiences and insights openly, write them in your journal or simply listen and work through things internally. this is a judgment-free zone, and a space full of love and healing energy. the deep sense of relief from release, the empowerment from your courageousness, and the love from supportive peers can bring so much hope and healing that can change our lives in beautiful ways.
•

in session 2, we will: ✨assess how we may re-create trauma in our lives
✨identify ways to reclaim our safety
✨identify how to listen to our bodies to better control our responses to triggers
✨learn ways to process emotions
✨establish a clear connection between the emotions and physical body responses
✨learn new destressing techniques

rsvp at iamthecreatress.com/ourevents 💕
•
•

text:
🇾​🇴​🇺​·🇷​🇪​ 🇮​🇳​🇻​🇮​🇹​🇪​🇩​ to the gauteng south launch of..
🦋𝐓𝐮𝐫𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠ᴘᴏɪɴᴛ🦋 🗓sat, 16 march 2019
🕑2:00pm
🏢butterfly hall, rietvlei zoo farm, 101 swartkoppies rd, mulbarton
🎟 *_free to attend. rsvp essential_*
📝sponsorship & marketing opportunities welcome. ༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄ founded by dr anneline chetty; turning point is a program that was envisioned from the recently launched #metoo! initiative, which advocates for survivors of both physical and sexual abuse to band together in one voice and to break the silence surrounding sexual harassment or physical assault. this program is intended to help women overcome past trauma and promote emotional growth and restoration in an emotionally supportive environment. it also empowers women to become self-reliant in order to make informed decisions about their choices, evaluate their choices, and take 
responsibility for their choices. *goals* • to provide women with an opportunity to address past trauma through a therapeutic and skills-based experiential model • to promote emotional growth and reparation in an emotionally supportive environment • to provide learning opportunities through a non-judgmental and experiential process • to empower women to become self-reliant in order to make informed decisions about their choices, evaluate their choices, and take responsibility for their choices. *outcomes* • improve verbal and non-verbal communication skills • improve problem-solving skills • increase assertiveness • improve self-esteem by helping them to feel good about themselves, develop their self-worth and increase their level of self-confidence • strengthen and develop their ability to trust in themselves and others • develop a healthier understanding of interpersonal relationships • increase self-awareness and personal insights • help empower them financially by equipping them with the necessary skills 
the overall plan is to include an entrepreneurial element to it with the rationale being that a woman who is empowered economically does not have to subject herself to abuse. 📲 *rsvp or more info*

🇾​🇴​🇺​·🇷​🇪​ 🇮​🇳​🇻​🇮​🇹​🇪​🇩​ to the gauteng south launch of..
🦋𝐓𝐮𝐫𝐧𝐢𝐧𝐠ᴘᴏɪɴᴛ🦋 🗓sat, 16 march 2019
🕑2:00pm
🏢butterfly hall, rietvlei zoo farm, 101 swartkoppies rd, mulbarton
🎟 *_free to attend. rsvp essential_*
📝sponsorship & marketing opportunities welcome. ༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄༄ founded by dr anneline chetty; turning point is a program that was envisioned from the recently launched #metoo! initiative, which advocates for survivors of both physical and sexual abuse to band together in one voice and to break the silence surrounding sexual harassment or physical assault. this program is intended to help women overcome past trauma and promote emotional growth and restoration in an emotionally supportive environment. it also empowers women to become self-reliant in order to make informed decisions about their choices, evaluate their choices, and take 
responsibility for their choices. *goals* • to provide women with an opportunity to address past trauma through a therapeutic and skills-based experiential model • to promote emotional growth and reparation in an emotionally supportive environment • to provide learning opportunities through a non-judgmental and experiential process • to empower women to become self-reliant in order to make informed decisions about their choices, evaluate their choices, and take responsibility for their choices. *outcomes* • improve verbal and non-verbal communication skills • improve problem-solving skills • increase assertiveness • improve self-esteem by helping them to feel good about themselves, develop their self-worth and increase their level of self-confidence • strengthen and develop their ability to trust in themselves and others • develop a healthier understanding of interpersonal relationships • increase self-awareness and personal insights • help empower them financially by equipping them with the necessary skills 
the overall plan is to include an entrepreneurial element to it with the rationale being that a woman who is empowered economically does not have to subject herself to abuse. 📲 *rsvp or more info*

text_retweet:
posted @withrepost • @sallycredence girls will be...a mother-daughter love story about a sexually curious teen and her anxious mom discover the value of trust and how to break the cycle.

residing in a fictional small, conservative town in indiana, annie wants to explore her sexuality. grace baxter wants to protect her daughter from the high-stakes that comes with being female. when annie's caught making out with her boyfriend, grace's past comes to the surface and the mother-daughter roller coaster begins. grace must reckon with her haunting memories of sex, abortion, and expectations of women prior to the #metoo movement, while annie gets answers for why her mom's such a tight-ass. after all, it's just sex...isn't it? #writingcommunity #womensupportwomen #womenempowerment #womenwriters #prochoice #metoo #sexeducation #reproductiverights #plannedparenthood #parenting #motherhood #opencommunication

text:
maybe i should have tried harder with therapy. maybe i could have given counseling a second, third, fourth shot. maybe i would have been able to transform my life and deal with my emotional baggage better. or maybe? i’m doing what’s best for me. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
people tell me that bottling up feelings is a bad thing to do. but is it really all that bad when i get to make it by 98% of my days just fine? how am i supposed to know the difference between doing what works for me, and doing something that’s “unhealthy”? bigger question— is repression..even all that bad?
⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀
i know many people who would definitely beg to differ with this post, but i’m just giving my earnest, open thoughts. i recognize that forgetting isn’t a permanent solution, because who can ever really forget the things that break them? but forgetting means surviving, and the way i see it is that at least surviving is living. obviously one day, i’d like to do more than just survive. but for the time being, i think this quote is pretty important and undoubtedly applicable to my life. ⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀⠀

text:
we need to stop killing animals 😞😔💔 rp  @vswolf @thecrueltycollective location: farmer johns , vernon california 
date: //february 21, 2019//
-
————————————————-
this video was taken at the pig vigil held at farmer johns’ slaughterhouse.
-
the vigil at this location yesterday was organized by @animalalliancenetwork
-
all of the pigs arriving here in the slaughter trucks, are 6 months old.
-
the individual in this clip was terrified. there were scratches all over her neck and covering her body from being prodded into the truck.
-
it is not unusual at these vigils to hear pigs screaming and trampling each other out of terror.
-
since the pigs are considered nothing more than a product to the industry, they previously have experienced nothing but violence, which is considered “common practice” up to the point of their deaths.
-
farmer johns’ slaughterhouse in vernon, slaughters around 7,000 pigs a day.
-
-
footage: @meatlessmolly -
-

genom att man delar upp offer i hora/madonna likt samhället delar upp kvinnor i hora/madonna. jag spottar på uppdelningen traffickingoffer/prostituerad pga männens våld mot oss är likadant. jag spottar på uppdelningen för att ett uppenbart och mer behjärtansvärt tvång är mer legitimt i privvade fönstertittares ögon än dom dolda tvången som handlar om uteslutning, klass och psykisk ohälsa. jag spottar på uppdelningen för att hjälporganisationer riktar in sig på just trafficking när alla som säljer sex till män lever i samma trauma, går på samma gator, löper lika stor risk, upplever lika mycket press eller ofrivillighet. jag spottar på uppdelningen för att torskar använder den för att ursäkta sig när dom köper sex av en psykiskt sjuk, svenskfödd, traumatiserad eller ekonomiskt tvingad tjej och menar att det ”iaf inte är någon som tvingar henne med dödshot”. jag spottar på uppdelningen för att den graderar övergrepp som ser likadana ut som grövre eller mindre grova. jag spottar på uppdelningen för att den flyttar fokus från torsk till hora. från männen till oss som säljer. den flyttar fokus från torskens agerande till vår nivå av egen agens. vi är inte agenter i våra egna liv, när vi av olika skäl går på gatan och hoppas att någon köper oss fastän vi vill det minst av allt. vi delar alla samma motvilja och känsla av tvång, av olika orsaker. det gemensamma vi har är att männen utnyttjar vår desperation. den kan se väldigt olik ut, men ingenting gör oss till mer eller mindre offer för dom män som utnyttjar oss. uppdelningen trafficking/prostitution är torskarnas bästa uppdelning av vilka personer man får köpa och förnedra, och vilka man inte får. dom som inte har en pistol i tinningen eller är fysiskt tvingade av en hallick ses som fair game. och precis där finns ett svinn av människor som man inte såg behövde exakt samma hjälp och stöd som dom ”giltigt utsatta”. dom ogiltiga offren. #intedinhora #prostitution #metoo

text: mouth full of blood is the latest body of work from toni morrison; a timely collection of essays and speeches on gender, race, politics, and truth, it brings together notable works from the past four decades. amid trump, brexit, the refugee crisis, black lives matter and #metoo however, morrison’s words feel timely, urgent. the book is divided into three parts, introduced respectively by a prayer for the 9/11 dead, a meditation on martin luther king and a moving eulogy for her friend, the writer james baldwin. it is a beautifully crafted text - you’d expect no less from a nobel and pulitzer prize-winning writer - which speaks directly to readers in 2019. to be consumed on a slow sunday afternoon, with a sizeable helping of time for reflection, mouth full of blood is out now. #stylereads by @alice_khabib

text:
scholarship announcement 💛
•
we have a feature article coming out with a fantastic company (that we are keeping a secret until it goes live) on monday. in honor of our mystery article, we are thrilled to announce our second @onthemendretreat scholarship, for a value of 20% off.
•
we want you to join us in a cozy and serene lodge high up in the california mountains, to take in the sunrise amongst the joshua tree desert. we want you to unplug, move inward, flow & stretch, break bread and form community over fireside chats and nourishing meals. we want you to find peace, forgiveness, acceptance and to free yourself from past heartache. sounds like a dream right? if you can envision it, we want to support you in making that dream a reality.
•
we are now accepting submissions through 3.2.19. to enter:
👉🏻 visit the “on the mend idyllwild” link in our bio
👉🏻 join seek retreat
👉🏻 press “request booking” to apply for the retreat (no payment needed)
👉🏻 submit your response in the text box, explaining why this healing retreat is so important to you!
•• we will announce the winner on 3.4.19. we can’t wait to get to know you all more, and walk alongside you in this journey!
•
**those who have already signed up or applied for the retreat are not eligible to apply for this scholarship.
•
•
•
•

text_retweet:
he's lost his position, his social standing, and millions of people hate him now. that's a lot more than these #metoo mfs get. it took twenty years to out weinstein and r.kelly. jussie lied. it cost him everything. everything. in two weeks flat. sure, he'll be used as a talking and reference point for "crazy liberal agendas" on fox news for a while. big deal. we are ok. we are fine. he isn't. let him heal. we've all lied. his was just preposterous and disrespectful af. you've never been disrespectful? none of y'all know the pressures of fame. you couldn't handle it. i've never been anything close to famous but even just the pressures of being an artist who has fans and whom people want to get a piece of and suffering from the debilitation of folks trying to steal my energy at every turn, just as a local artist who did a cameo on a reality show was overwhelming for me at times. that shit is tough. i wouldn't wish jussie smollett's position on anyone, not even my worst enemy if i had them.  forgive him as you would be forgiven. 
praying for you jussie. may the spirit of our god and father help you to find your way back✝️

text: i wrote about the strategies i use to write in a way that feels therapeutic to me and my healing. these are some of the strategies i share in my writing through healing workshops, in hopes that if you are a survivor thinking about writing that this can help make it feel a little easier to get started or keep going.  therapeutic writing and storytelling has been around since forever. it is a practice really developed by and grounded in the history of black and indigenous women, so l haven’t invented anything new, i just want to share with you what i’ve learned about what kind of writing feels support and therapeutic to my healing. link in bio. #metoo #ptsd #csa 📷 @mariahmirandaphoto

does anyone else think its corruption when the board that decides if someone poses a risk to patients is run by the father of that "doctor"? so dr. james orsini sr helps to decide if dr. james orsini jr has done anything negligent or wrong because he sits on the medical review board. wow, that is literally insane nepotism at its worst.  welcome to the abuse i fled in new jersey.  i  reported the behaviour a long time ago, i did in 2013, and i have again in 2017 and 2018. if anyone goes to essex oncology in nj and is harmed by this man, dr. james orsini, here is what you need to fight back against improper billing, improper treatment or misconduct.  i have posted those videos on you tube under threat of arrest to help you. i have posted videos where he shows his "bedside manner" and admits to being a pot head.  freedom of information is so very important. it's a constitutional right that i intend to use. #metoo
i am an instagram author and boston university college of communcations grad

by @annoying_ummi:

arewa  women are changing narratives and this time it’s on sexual assault and harassment. 
men in northern nigeria have always had it easy and the patriarchy has blossomed, forcing females to suffocate in marginalization. the patriarchy gave them the upper hand and made northern women into people stereotyped as intimidated and voiceless. the arewa woman has taken the backseat when it comes to integral issues in the society. there are reasons most northern women haven’t spoken and here are some of them:

shame
kina so ki bamu kunya? (you want to bring shame to us?) this is what a lot of survivors are asked when they report their perpetrators to their loved ones. your family places more importance on their place in the society than on your traumatic experience. you are told to seal your mouth to avoid being the topic of discussion in your neighborhood. the sad reality is that victims abused by their perpetrators are mostly family relations, and this has led to perpetrators roaming around freely, giving them more power. #arewametoo is here to end that.

blame game
as survivors are speaking up, some are asking why they visited their perpetrators, why they dressed a certain way, why they did not stay locked at home, why she slays. every time women speak up, they get blamed one way or the other. they are asked why they chatted with their perpetrators or why they were too cordial. the perpetrators are never questioned. we are tired of been shamed and feeling shamed. no one deserves to be assaulted or harassed sexually.

fear
the self-esteem of the average arewa girlchild is built to stay low. now, imagine the assaulted/harassed arewa girlchild — a ticking time bomb. a victim narrated her experience and what she was told by her aunt was, “no one is going to blame the guy because you have given away your integrity and that of your family, so better keep mute about this because it is not part of our culture and you don’t want to remain single for the rest of your life.” fear is always an obstacle.

continue reading on bellanaija.com/features #sexualassault #metoo #bellanaija

text:
r. kelly was charged friday with 10 counts of aggravated sexual abuse, after decades of lurid rumors and allegations that the r&b star was sexually abusing women and underage girls.
tandra simonton, spokeswoman for the cook county state’s attorney’s office, confirmed to the associated press the charges had been filed against the 52-year-old grammy winner but declined to say the specific number. media reports said there were 10 counts, all involving underage victims.

over the years, he has consistently denied any sexual misconduct.

kelly, whose legal name is robert kelly, is one of the top-selling recording artists of all time, with hits such as “i believe i can fly,” and his arrest sets the stage for another #metoo-era celebrity trial. bill cosby went to prison last year, and former hollywood studio boss harvey weinstein is awaiting trial.

kelly was charged a week after michael avenatti, the attorney whose clients have included porn star stormy daniels, said he recently gave chicago prosecutors new video evidence of the singer having sex with an underage girl. it was not immediately clear if the charges were connected to that video.
in 2008, a jury acquitted kelly of child pornography charges over a graphic video that prosecutors said showed him having sex with a girl as young as 13. he and the young woman allegedly depicted with him denied they were in the 27-minute video, even though the picture quality was good and witnesses testified it was them, and she did not take the stand. kelly could have gotten 15 years in prison.

legally and professionally, the walls began closing in on kelly more recently after the release of a bbc documentary about him last year and, last month, the multipart lifetime documentary “surviving r. kelly.” together they detailed allegations he was holding women against their will and running a “sex cult.” after the latest documentary, chicago’s top prosecutor, cook county state’s attorney kim foxx, said she was “sickened” by the allegations and asked potential victims to come forward.

text:
february 22 ,2016 ,i was followed by a man in this publix in miami ....that  day was one of the hardest days of my life.... i wasn’t aware of how the day would change me forever.  rewind to when i was walking into publix for a 5 minute trip to pick up my glutenfree chicken nuggets (lol when i still ate chicken) ketchup and a drink...i walked up isle 6 to get the ketchup and that’s when i saw him...he creeped me out so i left the ketchup and went to 1 for my publix lemonade....and wham i was close to running into him i walked around him like ugh ....then i went back to 6 grabbed my ketchup and “lost” him....or so i thought....i walked to the register paid for my food and exited out the right exit ....he was waiting on the left exit... he followed me to my car...i didn’t know what to do he was right behind me in broad day light.... i tried to get in the car as quickly as i could but in that quick movement he lifted my dress and grabbed my butt!!!! i went to swing at him and he dodged it ...honestly i don’t think my punch would have hurt him. he then looked me in the eye and said what are you going to do about it...and in that moment i thought to myself “what are you going to do eli? you’re not dreaming this really happened.....” and i screamed 911!! 911!!! 911!!! his eyes got so big i thought they were going to fall out of his sockets...he began to run through the parking lot...i ran after him!!!!!still screaming 911 (again i don’t really know what my plan was if i actually caught up to him) he got to his car and drove away with no license tag!!!!!! then the adrenaline deflated  and i just cried and cried and cried...the cops came and they really couldn’t do anything because they really didn’t have much. it was really frightening...but it taught me a lot! 
1. park in the front 
2. never text and walk in a parking lot (which i wasn’t doing) 
3. always be aware and alert 
4. i’m not a victim 
5. it doesn’t matter what you’re wearing if a bad person wants to do bad things to you they will and it’s not your fault! 
6. you have the power! you are not an easy target!

#metoo #youarenotalone

a graphic essay on the #metoo movement in india. 
this essay addresses sexual harassment at the workplace in india, and how many have reacted to it. 
it is a deeper look at the #metoo movement in india, for which i’ve collaborated with the polis project ( @thepolisproject ). if you think this message is important, relevant or have faced similar questions in discussions about the movement, please consider sharing this! 
the entire essay is available on the polis project’s website, and is linked in my bio. it’s best viewed on a larger screen, so pleaseee do me and your eyesight a favour and check it out on the website!

text:
in the music video “lose my mind,” my character aurora is alerted of a dangerous incoming threat through warning lights that go off throughout the spaceship. last year i called the national domestic abuse hotline on behalf of (and with permission from) a friend who knew something was off in their relationship but wasn’t sure if it was really crossing the line from difficult to dangerous and didn’t want the hotline number on their call log (a big warning sign in itself). i shared all the info i knew of the situation to an astonishingly kind operator who walked me through how certain warnings had indeed made the relationship begin to cross into “dangerous” and she offered practical steps and resources for how my friend could get out and what to do if things suddenly escalated along the way. the info wasn’t easy for my friend to accept but empowered them to take control and resulted in a hard-won happy ending. the call was completely free and anonymous - you don’t have to be in an immediate life-or-death situation to find out if red lights are warning you of a relationship starting to take a dangerous turn. 1-800-799-7233 is the nat’l domestic abuse hotline in the usa, and they’re 24 hours - i called at almost 11 pm. you and your loved ones have the right to be safe. more cheery posts on the way i promise! 😁😉 i just felt this was far too important not to share and want y’all to be empowered for yourself or someone you know who could use your help today. love you guys and have a safe and happy friday!! 💖🙏🏼🚀
.
.
.

text:
lisa borders, the ceo of time’s up, abruptly resigned her post this week after her son was accused of sexual assault, the organization told thewrap on thursday.

borders, who had been in the job just over three months, resigned this week citing “family concerns that require my singular focus.” but thewrap has learned that borders agreed to resign after her son dijon borders, a healer based in los angeles, was accused of sexual misconduct in a session with a woman who went to the police. her responses in defending her son made her position untenable, according to an individual with knowledge of the situation.

the individual told thewrap that “lisa wanted to take action to defend her son and in doing so was in conflict with her role leading an organization deeply rooted in supporting survivors.” in a statement, time’s up released: “on friday, lisa borders informed members of time’s up leadership that sexual assault allegations had been made against her son in a private forum. within 24 hours, lisa made the decision to resign as president and ceo of time’s up and we agreed that it was the right decision for all parties involved. all of our actions were fully guided by our support for survivors.

we respect the rights of all survivors to own their own stories. we strongly encourage anyone who has experienced sexual harassment, assault or related retaliation in the workplace or in trying to advance their careers to contact the time’s up legal defense fund for assistance.

we remain committed to our mission to create, safe and dignified for women of all kinds.“ read more below #metoo #timesup

text: please don’t put other people down. everyone is different and no one has the right to talk bad about others. you can be whoever you want or love whoever you want. always keep in mind that somebody loves and support you even if you don’t feel like it. if you feel sad because your lonely. somebody out there is just looking for a person like you. if you haven’t found your soulmate yet you will definitely find one in the future. i know it’s hard not to care about other people’s opinions but for the happiness of ourselves we shouldn’t care. it’s impossible to fit to everyone’s standards. if you feel ugly just know that someone out there thinks that your beautiful. as a teenager i struggled a lot about the way i looked but getting into feminism helped me realise that everyone is beautiful. so please remember that and support everyone!

text:
"anger itself is not a risk that breaks relationships. the real risk is that in expressing our anger we risk finding out the people around us simply don't care." soraya chemaly, @sorayachemaly at explore more summit 2019
.
when we open ourselves to more pleasure, we open ourselves to feeling more of everything. when we cut ourselves off from certain feelings, we cut ourselves off from the potential depth of our pleasure.
.
anger is an incredible emotion that sadly is policed, minimized, and denied in women and femmes. why? because anger is the emotion of fairness, autonomy, and justice. patriarchy & sexism just can't have that.
.
anger tends to our boundaries. anger notices when something doesn't feel right or fair, when we're over-extending ourselves, when we need something important.
.
the problem is that study after study after study show that men perceive women's anger as selfish. this means that often the response to a woman's anger is not concern or inquiry into why she's angry so that conditions can be changed but often the response is anger about her/their anger.
.
this is what soraya speaks to around the risks of anger. when we get angry, the risk is not being angry. the risk is in finding out that the things we see as unfair or important will not matter to the people around us, especially if we are women/femmes. we risk finding out that people only care when we are agreeable, pleasant, nice, or at a minimum, neutral and tolerating.
.
layer on top of this the complexities of race, culture, ability, age, class, and it becomes clear why so many women and femmes struggle with befriending their anger. .
join soraya and dozens of others at the 4th annual explore more summit as we explore power, pleasure, feelings, trauma, healing, burnout, and connection. it's a free conference that happens entirely online starting monday february 25th. register and join us today at exploremoresummit.com
.
#ragebecomesher #anger #metoo #patriarchy #feminist #feminism #ems2019

text_retweet:
if you're looking for a book to start a dialogue, look no further.

#repost @sallycredence (@get_repost)
・・・
girls will be...a mother-daughter love story about a sexually curious teen and her anxious mom discover the value of trust and how to break the cycle.

residing in a fictional small, conservative town in indiana, annie wants to explore her sexuality. grace baxter wants to protect her daughter from the high-stakes that comes with being female. when annie's caught making out with her boyfriend, grace's past comes to the surface and the mother-daughter roller coaster begins. grace must reckon with her haunting memories of sex, abortion, and expectations of women prior to the #metoo movement, while annie gets answers for why her mom's such a tight-ass. after all, it's just sex...isn't it? #writingcommunity #womensupportwomen #womenempowerment #womenwriters #prochoice #metoo #sexeducation #reproductiverights #plannedparenthood #parenting #motherhood #opencommunication

this #femalefounderfriday we're highlighting anu duggal founder of the female founders fund.

early in her career, @anuduggal founded two businesses in india, and helped to raise millions of dollars in venture-capital funding. but after she moved to new york city in 2011, she witnessed female entrepreneurs struggling to find backing, community, and support. she vowed to do something about the situation, starting @fcubedvc to prove that women make excellent founders. realizing that goal, though, would prove to be a long, difficult slog. --as told to @youfoundchristine of @incmagazine.

text:
#fbf to right before i was diagnosed with hypothyroidism. i gained 15lbs in about 3 weeks and i was having panic attacks like they were square meals. this was at an award ceremony for work where i was supposed to win employee of the year but lost it because of semantics. i worked my ass off that year. the sexual harassment and mental abuse from clients, the gaslighting from hr, the dismissal from my manager all felt like it was for nothing. i crashed - physically - after losing. i was also going through some personal heartbreak. - this was a lot. i ended up taking a v long overnight drive from cleveland to philly and fell so inspired by one of my bffs. .
.
.
when life treats you like shit, show up looking like you’re the shit. 💪💕 .
.
.
.
.

text:
dearman skill: the most effective way to make a request 
d - describe the situation in a simple way using facts .
.

e - express how you are feeling. use “i” .
.

a -assert by stating no firmly or asking for your need .
.

r - reinforce by making the person know why they should grant your request .
.

m - mindful, stay focused on the conversation .
.

a - appear confident regardless of your feelings inside .
. 
n - negotiate, you aren’t demanding anything you are asking. come up with a solution that works for both of you, but remember no means no and not to be persuaded .
.

these skills can be applied through all situations, not only in a relationship. 
#believeinyourvoice .
.
.

girls will be...a mother-daughter love story about a sexually curious teen and her anxious mom discover the value of trust and how to break the cycle.

residing in a fictional small, conservative town in indiana, annie wants to explore her sexuality. grace baxter wants to protect her daughter from the high-stakes that comes with being female. when annie's caught making out with her boyfriend, grace's past comes to the surface and the mother-daughter roller coaster begins. grace must reckon with her haunting memories of sex, abortion, and expectations of women prior to the #metoo movement, while annie gets answers for why her mom's such a tight-ass. after all, it's just sex...isn't it? #writingcommunity #womensupportwomen #womenempowerment #womenwriters #prochoice #metoo #sexeducation #reproductiverights #plannedparenthood #parenting #motherhood #opencommunication

text_retweet:
#repost @saturnsistersofficial with @get_repost
・・・
the breaking news on friday (venus day) is brought to us by tonight’s intensely potent pluto/venus conjunction in capricorn. sometimes it really feels like the planets are writing the news, and this is one of those days. since late last night, three major stories have broken revealing sex crimes committed by men in power – and all are getting the karmic retribution they deserve, served fresh by pluto, planet of reckonings.

first the handling of a case against #jeffreyepstein, notorious pedophile and child rapist (and not incidentally, a good friend of #donaldtrump) was deemed a crime. and this is also not incidental in the least – the man who allowed epstein to get off with a slap on the wrist and left his victims without justice – he just happens to be trump’s current labor secretary, alex acosta. now the victims can finally pursue their cases, long after they were raped and used as sex slaves, when they were young teens. next, a sex trafficking ring was broken up in jupiter, florida, about 20 minutes away from mar-a-lago. it ensnared #robertcraft, the owner of the patriots and you guessed it – a friend of trump’s. shortly after, #rkelly was finally indicted for his long history of pedophilia. 
as someone on twitter said midday on friday -- “today is like scumbag woodstock.” the astrological backbone of this evolving news cycle is pluto, ruler of karma, secrets, the illicit and forbidden – and yes, sometimes the planet of criminal acts. note that the key commonality between the three men involved in today’s news is an aggregation of great wealth – this is key.

note: 2024 brings the first pluto return ever for america, and the transit is long – we’re in it already. today’s news is a drop in the bucket, but it distills the theme – we’re watching our culture transform into one of justice for all the people who’ve been trampled, used, enslaved and harmed by the men who’ve abused their power. #metoo is part of this. #blacklivesmatter is part of this. indigenous rights and the fight against climate change: they’re all a part of this. 
full article on saturnsisters.com
name: Stefanie Iris Weiss

text:
encourage a sister!!💞 what's your country's story? 
in england, "witchcraft" was criminalised in 1542 and thereafter a series of hunts were led that ended in the execution of over 500 women until its decriminalisation. around the period of the civil war this continued to increase along with other heretics. interestingly enough, while witchcraft applies to the act of conjurations and things of the sort and not to a particular gender, men were only rarely victims of this persecution. this privilege of men not being stigmatised for what is seen as inferiority consistently has persisted. this comes from positions of power which even to this day are mainly always held by men, this roots at the patriarchy that many people like to hide as something of the past but do not realise it prevails. the #metoo movement aimed to tackle the silencing of our women and the ways in which it is being reproached, is sickening and a reminder of all the changes we still have to make. the fight isn't over. this goes to encourage women to rise and to break the barriers that years of political imbalance have caused!!

text:
we're thrilled to be promoting the documentary, "catching sight of thelma & louise." the film is a powerful, authentic exploration of women’s experiences in the world. clips from the movie "thelma & louise" serve as a backdrop for intimate stories by viewers who saw the iconic hollywood film in 1991 and wrote letters about their reactions at that time. these same women and men were tracked down to share what the film means to them today. the documentary is particularly relevant in the #metoo era and director/producer jennifer townsend is aiming to reignite a conversation that begins with the question: "is the world finally ready to believe thelma & louise? . "catching sight of thelma & louise" is making its north american theatrical debut at @cinemavillage in new york city on april 5th. link to the trailer in bio .

#catchingsightofthelmaandlouise #metoo #thelmaandlouise #thelmaandlouiseroadtrip
#cinemavillage #jennifertownsend

text:
did you know? according to rainn, roughly 23% of undergraduate women and 5.5% of undergraduate men experience sexual assault.

that number is way too high and it's time to do something about it.

first things first, welcome to the "official" look us in the eyes instagram page. i want to extend a big thank you to everyone who has or will follow us. for those of you who are new, let me introduce myself and this page.

my name is katerina and i'm just one of the many amazing people who makes up this group, and one of just a few admins on this account.

luite is a student run organization at the university of maine farmington. formed in response to the mishandling of sexual assault cases on campus, luite believes it is time to address this issue head on. our mission is to bring attention to the issue of sexual assault on campus and fix these issues so current and future students can feel safe on campus. too often, schools side with perpetrators, leaving victims feeling scared, confused, and angry.

we are not blaming the school for our assaults, but we recognize that the way title ix cases are handled is flawed. it is up to us to make change, and it starts right here at umf.

on this account we will be posting images from past and future events, sexual health and safety infographics, and other things.

if you want to know more about our cause or how you can contribute, head on over to facebook and find us under the same name. in the meantime, keep your eyes peeled for new posts!

cheers,
katerina

#lookusintheeyes #luite #metoo #wetoo

text:
it’s been one of the messiest oscar races of recent years, fuelling old cinematic feuds along cultural and commercial lines.
.
it has pitted a netflix production against a studio establishment wary of a streaming-dominated future.
.
it’s elevated daring movies by black directors, but it also gave us the driving miss daisy of 2018, a supposedly feel-good but widely controversial story of a white man’s journey to tolerance.
.
and looming in the background of it all is #metoo, a movement given new life by sexual-assault allegations against the director of one of the best-picture nominees.
.
it all comes to a head on sunday night, when the 92nd academy awards kicks off at hollywood’s dolby theater.
.
follow the link in our bio (for subscribers) for barry hertz's overview of who is likely to win, and who will deserve to.
.
.
@theacademy #oscars

liebe meine freundinnen, mein kleine #metoo
わたしの愛する友人たちへ、ちいさな #metoo

先週から今週にかけて、ウィメンズ・マーチだの、 #metoo だの、女性のムーブメントをテーマに記事を書いたものだから、自分が女性であることについて、なんとなく向き合った1週間でもあった。幸い性暴力を受けた経験はないけれど、セクシュアルハラスメントにあったことは何度もある。たとえば、触られたくないところを触られたとき、自分自身はいちいち気にするほうではないと思っていたけれど、よくよく思い返したら、いやだけど問題にするのは面倒くさいから我慢しただけ、という感情のほうが正しい気がする。ドイツの性教育は「どこを触られたらいやか？」ということから授業がスタートすると知人から聞いたことがあるのだけど、いやぁ、やっぱりそうあるべきだよね、と妙に納得してしまうのであった。

かと言って、女性に生まれたことを後悔していないし、むしろわたしは女性でよかったと思っている。その一方で、なんで毎月生理痛に悩まされなきゃいけないの！ と叫んでいる自分もいる。デュッセルドルフで働き出してから、毎回の月経で胃腸炎のような状態になってしまうので、昨年秋にドイツではじめて産婦人科に足を運んだ。そのときに最終手段として低用量ピルを処方してもらったのだが、やはり排卵しない身体なんて自然じゃない、という考えから服用に抵抗があった。でも、このままでは毎月仕事を休むことになりかねない……。そんなわけで、ついに今週から飲んでみる決心がついたのだった。効くかどうかはわからない。でも、これで改善するのなら試してみる価値は十分にある。まずは毎日忘れずに飲むを目標に！

memo：日本だと低用量ピルは21日分の1シートが2000〜3000円すると聞いたけど、ドイツでは3シートで18ユーロ（約2300円）ほど。値段自体も服用のハードルを下げているのかも。

text:
r. kelly’s attorney says the singer is “shell-shocked” by the aggravated sexual abuse indictment against him and plans to turn himself in to authorities friday night.

steve greenberg told the associated press that his client is “extraordinarily disappointed and depressed” by the 10 counts chicago prosecutors filed against him.

greenberg said he had offered to sit down with prosecutors before charges were filed to discuss “why these charges are baseless.” but they refused, he said.

r. kelly maintains his innocence.

he is set for a bond hearing tomorrow after judge authorized a no-bail arrest warrant.

via associated press

text:
speak up. speak out. be you.
•
in the past i would internalize my feelings...a lot. never wanting to rock the boat or get into any sort of confrontation whatsoever. however always internalizing your feelings is not healthy for your mind or body. it can eat you up inside. learn to speak up for the things that matter to you.
•
nowadays i make sure that i’m heard when i feel it’s necessary. i don’t shy away from sharing my opinion, thoughts or beliefs. i speak up for myself and for the values i believe in. i speak up for others. •
i still find it hard sometimes. it can and still is a bit out of my comfort zone. but personal growth can be uncomfortable.
•
in the end...your voice is your freedom; use it.
